The membership of the council shall consist of:
The commissioner of the Department of Corrections, ex officio;
The compact administrator of the Department of Corrections, ex officio;
The deputy commissioner of the Office of Community Services and Facilities, ex officio;
One (1) member of the House of Representatives selected by the Speaker of the House of Representatives and appointed by the Governor;
One (1) member of the Senate selected by the President of the Senate and appointed by the Governor;
Two (2) members of the judiciary selected by the Chief Justice of the Kentucky Supreme Court and appointed by the Governor; and
Six (6) at-large members, appointed by the Governor, representing victim groups and other community interest groups.

The Kentucky Council for Interstate Adult Offender Supervision shall meet at least annually, at the call of the chair, and shall:
Advocate when seeking resources;
Provide recommendations regarding operational improvements;
Provide recommendations regarding dispute resolution;
Provide recommendations regarding training needs;
Provide recommendations regarding policy changes; and
Serve as a support mechanism for the Kentucky Compact Office.
